  "id": "CENTRAL-CODE-ON-WAGES",
  "name": "Code on Wages, 2019",
  "shortName": "Code on Wages",
  "officialCitation": "The Code on Wages, 2019 (Act No. 29 of 2019), effective from 21 November 2025.",
  "overview": "The Code on Wages, 2019 consolidates the central legal framework for minimum wages, payment of wages, statutory bonus and gender-based wage equality. It became operative on 21 November 2025. The Code on Wages (Central) Rules, 2026 apply where the Central Government is the appropriate government; establishments governed by a State or Union Territory must apply the corresponding local rules, wage notifications and authorities. Notifications and actions under the repealed wage enactments continue only to the extent preserved by section 69 and not inconsistent with the Code.",
